From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: arch <arch@localhost>
Date: Sun, 8 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] arm64: dts: qcom: platina: add qcom,msm-id for modem
 stability

Add qcom,msm-id property to the Xiaomi Mi 8 Lite (platina) device tree.
This property is read by the MPSS (modem) firmware during boot to validate
the platform. Without it, the modem firmware crashes every ~40 seconds
with "fatal error without message".

The msm-id value 317 (0x13d) corresponds to the SDM660 SoC, as defined
in the Android kernel source for this platform (MiCode/Xiaomi_Kernel_OpenSource,
platina-o-oss branch).

This fix is essential for WiFi to work, since the WCN3990 WiFi chip runs
as a protection domain inside the MPSS subsystem. A stable modem is a
prerequisite for WiFi functionality.

Signed-off-by: arch <arch@localhost>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sdm660-xiaomi-platina.dts | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sdm660-xiaomi-platina.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sdm660-xiaomi-platina.dts
index xxxxxxx..xxxxxxx 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sdm660-xiaomi-platina.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sdm660-xiaomi-platina.dts
@@ -19,6 +19,7 @@
 / {
 	model = "Xiaomi Mi 8 Lite";
 	compatible = "xiaomi,platina", "qcom,sdm660";
+	qcom,msm-id = <317 0x0>;
 	chassis-type = "handset";
 
 	aliases {
-- 
